    "narrative": "For today\u2019s slate, **Taylor Ward** stands out as our premier start with an elite 71.46 efficiency score. The combination of a favorable matchup against McCullers Jr. (4.94 xERA) and a significant park factor boost makes him an essential anchor in the outfield. **Bryson Stott** mirrors this strength with a 70.72 score; his efficiency is driven by a strong platoon advantage against Houser and a move up to the five-hole, which optimizes his RBI potential. We are also leaning heavily into our speed-focused strategy today, as **Jeremiah Jackson** and **Tyler Freeman** provide excellent value. Despite a lower spot in the order, **Jeremiah Jackson** benefits from a high-upside matchup against McCullers Jr. and a slow delivery profile from the mound that creates a high probability for stolen bases\u2014our scarcest and most coveted category.\n\nThe bench decision process was tight, with **Jung Hoo Lee** missing the cut by a hair at 39.92. While his profile usually provides a stable floor, the platoon disadvantage against the lefty Mayza dropped his projection just below our 40.0 \"Zebras Floor.\" We are playing it safe to preserve game caps, especially since **Masyn Winn** barely cleared the threshold at 40.75 despite drawing the difficult assignment of Skenes. We must remain cautious with **Geraldo Perdomo** and **Masyn Winn**, as both face elite arms with sub-3.10 xERA ratings; their scores are suppressed by the opposing pitcher's skill, necessitating a watchful eye on in-game performance. With **Jos\u00e9 Ram\u00edrez** and **Cal Raleigh** enjoying a scheduled day off, we are maximizing our active roster efficiency by prioritizing platoon splits and park factors across the board, ensuring our sprint-speed assets like **Jeremiah Jackson** and **Tyler Freeman** remain in prime positions to capitalize on defensive weaknesses.",
